indicator-sensors (0.5-1) saucy; urgency=low

  * Update to 0.5 release
     - Add customizable hysteresis to alarms to avoid showing then
       hiding quickly
     - Potential bug fixes found with clang-analyzer
     - Export full icon path over DBus - for icons in GNOME Shell extension
     - Add notification filtering support for GNOME Shell 3.8
     - Add an AppData XML description for GNOME Software
     - Updated and added new translations from Launchpad - he and zh_CN
     - Addition of udisks2 plugin to provide disk temperatures on latest Fedora / Ubuntu
     - Workaround bug in aticonfig package to avoid lock up - LP bug #1016896
     - Fixup some untranslated strings to be shown translated - LP bug #1087150
     - Fix crash when unselecting all sensors - LP bug #1086102
     - Fix oversized sensor properties window - LP bug #1094723
     - Cleanup display of temperature values - LP bug #1077754

 -- Alex Murray <murray.alex@gmail.com>  Sat, 02 Nov 2013 23:20:00 +1030

indicator-sensors (0.3-1) quantal; urgency=low

  * Update to 0.3 release
    - Support for building the nvidia plugin on Fedora
    - Proper translations support
    - Use persistent notifications to enable better interaction (LP bug #1052329)
    - Fix bug where we mangled Fahrenheit values (LP bug #1052939)
    - Fix bug where alarms would show on startup before sensors had been initialised (LP bug #1009881 and LP bug #1017275)
    - Fix bug that caused the first sensor to always be shown as the active sensor (LP bug #1009909)

